&lt;p&gt;Descript is the AI-powered video and podcast editor that makes editing as easy as editing a document. As we continue to grow our Enterprise business, we&#39;re looking for a Product Marketing Manager to help define how we bring our products to market, enable our sales team, and turn product innovation into revenue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t a traditional launch marketing role. You&#39;ll own the ongoing narrative for Enterprise: Building messaging, sales enablement, competitive strategy, and the systems that help our GTM teams win. You&#39;ll partner closely with Product, Sales, RevOps, Customer Success, and Support to shape how customers discover, evaluate, and buy Descript.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you enjoy building from scratch, making strategic tradeoffs, and tying your work directly to pipeline, we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own positioning and messaging for Enterprise products and solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and continuously improve our sales enablement engine, including battlecards, competitive intelligence, ROI messaging, and playbooks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales and RevOps to turn customer conversations and Gong insights into better messaging and higher win rates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Product to influence roadmap, launches, pricing, and packaging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help define and scale our Enterprise GTM motion, including upcoming initiatives around our API platform and AI-powered products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build systems—not just launches—that connect product marketing to measurable business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4–6 years of B2B SaaS Product Marketing experience with ownership of Enterprise GTM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience partnering closely with Enterprise Sales on messaging and enablement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent writer with strong strategic thinking and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable making recommendations, driving alignment, and navigating ambiguity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly cross-functional, with experience working across Product, Sales, Customer Success, and Marketing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excited by building processes and operating in a fast-moving environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with APIs or technical products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pricing and packaging experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-native workflows and a passion for using AI to work more effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in creator tools, media, or PLG companies expanding into Enterprise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base salary range for this role is $145k - $165k/year. Final offer amounts will carefully consider multiple factors, including prior experience, expertise, location, level, and may vary from the amount above.&lt;/p&gt;
